Write a function that returns the product of all the numbers in a list 
 ;; product : List -> Number
    ;; Returns the product of the numbers in the given list
    ;; Examples: 
    ;; (product empty) = 0
    ;; (product (list 1)) = 1
    ;; (product (list 1 2 3) = 6
    (define (product lst)
      (cond
        [(empty? lst) 0]
        [else (* (first lst) (product (rest lst)))]))